What is Digital Precision Construction & Manufacturing?
Digital precision construction & manufacturing (DPCM) refers to a technology‑driven workflow that combines high‑resolution 3‑D scanning, BIM‑enabled design, AI‑powered analytics, and autonomous fabrication equipment to produce building components with millimetre‑level tolerances. By synchronising design intent with real‑time site data, DPCM reduces rework, minimises material waste, and shortens project delivery cycles. The approach supports both prefabricated modular construction and on‑site robotic assembly, making it applicable across a wide spectrum of infrastructure, commercial, and residential projects.
